description: To visually display the current state of land use in the city. The code 9999 refers to parcels that the City has not yet designated. They are almost always in new subdivisions. A detail description of these codes can be found at: https://docs.google.com/a/edmonton.ca/file/d/0B2-9njwn6euHNnZBaWp4NjdpbWc/edit
